money arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe for students money for groups start by making a budget think of every expense your project could possibly have and then overshoot a little bit how much money does your group have already what are the essentials for the event make an excel or word document with each expense called a line item and your projected cost do sub totals and overall totals things to consider will your event pay for itself if you are expecting revenue project that with a conservative estimate for example that only half of your tickets are sold always remember to budget for reserving space and space supervision advertising print materials like programs administrative materials like tape or copies etc art materials finding funding as a student group you will most likely be looking for funding for your creative endeavors the best way to learn about funding is through the student activities and leadership office some primary student group funding sources include assu special fees assu senate appropriations committee assu graduate student council stanford sponsored program funding ssfd you might also consider approaching student organizations academic departments the haas center or community resource centers for co sponsorship if your events seem particularly relevant to them for individual projects stanford offers several channels through which artists can find funding for their projects see the list below for short descriptions to find which is the most appropriate for you student arts grant program sica and the student arts grant board provide grants for undergraduates and graduate students to do extra curricular creative projects click here to learn more about student arts grants undergraduate advising and research grants undergraduate advising and research provides student grants to support original independent creation in all media please note that these grants are not available for student groups visit the undergraduate academic life website for more information departmental funding many departments may offer discretionary funds to assist with individual arts projects students should speak to the student services representative in their department about this possibility where possible clearly map out the goals of your project and create a sample budget to estimate your costs before bringing your idea to a departmental office prospective students check out the arts guide your multimedia guide to the arts at stanford stay updated student home events calendar opportunities in review subscribe curricular info majoring minoring creativity course guide arts intensive arts immersion arts circle make it happen money supplies space collaboration promotion beyond stanford internships career resources bay area arts back to arts at stanford make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
